text.tspan: Basic arch of BNN where connections between layers is defined in software,
though the sizes of the layers and their neurons are defined by hw parameters.
All weights, thresholds, input and output data are stored in memory.
BNN can be trained on FPGA while also running quickly/efficiently.
Process can be started on interrupt or with sw write.
Simple interrupts are used to schedule between blocks.
Easy to pause, inspect progress, debug with sw on riscv or external debugger.
